[0m[49m[38;5;10m+     69[0m:[38;5;10m[49m   2. **The crisis-screening classifier is a separately-validated pipeline.** The architecture should specify the held-out crisis-presentation-corpus discipline (curated and reviewed by licensed mental-health clinicians, kept current with literature, validated before launch and on each material update; covers crisis-language variants by language, by demographic cohort, by condition, and by adversarial-test scenarios), per-cohort sensitivity targets, false-negative rate as launch-gate metric (target less than 2%, ideally under 1% for high-risk dimensions per the recipe's TODO marker), false-positive rate as operational-efficiency metric, per-classifier-version stamping on every conversation, and quarterly clinical-leadership review of held-out-corpus performance.
